f fish measured in the initial SMAST Study Fleet Program, while the simulation method suggests that for most groundfish species reducing the total number of fish to 20{\%} will not affect the variance, skewness, and kurtosis of the population length. For the SMAST Study Fleet Program, increasing the number of sampling stations can improve sampling precision better than increasing the number of fish measured within each station. This study helps to develop an optimal sampling design that balances the quality of the data collected and costs of the sampling effort. Received July 31, 2011; accepted August 11, 2012},
